<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chp_riemann_sums_and_area_approximation">
  <title>Riemann Sums and Approximations of Area</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      In this tutorial,
      we use numerical approximation to calculate definite integrals
      (namely, the right-sum, left-sum,
      midpoint, Simpson's, and trapezoidal methods).
      We then calculate these definite integrals using the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus.
      We will also learn how to find indefinite integrals as functions.
    </p>
  </introduction>
